Package: FTPD
Version: 1.0.0
Maintainer: mgrossmann
Depends:
Homepage: https://github.com/mvslovers/ftpd
Description: MVS 3.8J FTPD Server

This is the mvslovers/ftpd server: a full-featured FTP daemon for MVS
3.8j built from the ground up on crent370. Supports native MVS dataset
access, JES2 job submission/status/spool retrieval, and UFS files via
UFSD (soft dependency -- MVS and JES features work without it).

This package installs the FTPD load module into MVSLOVER.LOAD (the
shared mvslovers load library, created on first install), the STC
procedure into SYS2.PROCLIB(FTPD), and the default configuration into
SYS2.PARMLIB(FTPDPRM0). It replaces any prior FTPD package installed by
MVP. The STC runs with STEPLIB DSN=MVSLOVER.LOAD; nothing is added to
SYS2.LINKLIB (modules copied into a LNKLST library after IPL abend
S0C4 at fetch once the library takes a new extent). A stale FTPD
member from the previous package may remain in SYS2.LINKLIB -- the
STEPLIB shadows it, but you can delete it manually if you like.

Requires RAKF for authentication. Add user FTPD in group USER to
SYS1.SECURE.CNTL(USERS) and add a FTPAUTH profile to
SYS1.SECURE.CNTL(PROFILES) to control who may use FTP, then recycle
RAKF ('/S RAKF'). See the homepage's doc/FTPD_RAKF_SETUP.md for full
setup instructions.

To start the FTPD server run '/S FTPD' on the Hercules console. To stop
it run '/P FTPD'. Console commands: '/F FTPD,STATS|SESSIONS|CONFIG|
HELP|SHUTDOWN'. To change settings (port, IP, etc) edit
SYS2.PARMLIB(FTPDPRM0); the default listener port is 2121.
